{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876184023,"sessionID":"ses_2858832aeffeeNpWyuVMBY32Rn","part":{"id":"prt_d7a780e36001cTewT5XXSvNXHi","messageID":"msg_d7a77fc85001OyuUkvXSqzEbXp","sessionID":"ses_2858832aeffeeNpWyuVMBY32Rn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_3b3192c814164e83aaadfb87","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-022: CLI publish 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n6: **Language:** Python  \n7: **Size:** L  \n8: **Type:** Implementation of publish command for agent deployment to Kubernetes (AgentRuntime CR or standard Deployment/Service)\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** cli-toolkit/design.md, cli-toolkit/spec.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-022.1: Publish Command CLI Interface\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement the `publish` Typer subcommand with options for workspace, version, image repository credentials, deployment region, cloud provider, provider type (agentcube/k8s), node port, replicas, namespace, and verbose logging.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Publish command registration\n21: - **GIVEN** the Typer app is initialized\n22: - **WHEN** the CLI loads\n23: - **THEN** the `publish` subcommand SHALL be registered as `agentcube publish`\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Default workspace resolution\n26: - **GIVEN** user runs `agentcube publish` without `-f` flag\n27: - **WHEN** the command executes\n28: - **THEN** workspace SHALL resolve to current directory `\".\"`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Version specification\n31: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--version 1.2.3`\n32: - **WHEN** the command executes\n33: - **THEN** version SHALL override metadata version for publishing\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Image repository URL\n36: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--image-url registry.example.com/myimage`\n37: - **WHEN** the command executes in local build mode\n38: - **THEN** image URL SHALL be used for image push target\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Image repository credentials\n41: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--image-username` and `--image-password`\n42: - **WHEN** the command executes\n43: - **THEN** credentials SHALL be used for Docker login to image repository\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Provider selection\n46: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--provider k8s`\n47: - **WHEN** the command executes\n48: - **THEN** deployment SHALL use standard Kubernetes Deployment + NodePort Service\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Default AgentCube provider\n51: - **GIVEN** user does not specify `--provider`\n52: - **WHEN** the command executes\n53: - **THEN** provider SHALL default to `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR)\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: NodePort specification\n56: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--node-port 30080` with `--provider k8s`\n57: - **WHEN** the command executes\n58: - **THEN** Kubernetes Service SHALL use specified NodePort (30000-32767)\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Replicas specification\n61: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--replicas 3` with `--provider k8s`\n62: - **WHEN** the command executes\n63: - **THEN** Deployment SHALL be created with 3 replicas\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Namespace specification\n66: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--namespace production`\n67: - **WHEN** the command executes\n68: - **THEN** deployment SHALL target the `production` namespace\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Command-level verbose logging\n71: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--verbose` on publish command\n72: - **WHEN** the command executes\n73: - **THEN** logging level SHALL be DEBUG for publish operation only\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ### REQ-022.2: PublishRuntime Integration\n78: \n79: **Requirement:** The system SHALL instantiate `PublishRuntime` with verbose flag and provider, and invoke `publish()` method with workspace path and options.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: PublishRuntime instantiation\n82: - **GIVEN** publish command is invoked\n83: - **WHEN** command handler runs\n84: - **THEN** `PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)` SHALL be instantiated\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Pass options to PublishRuntime.publish\n87: - **GIVEN** CLI options are parsed\n88: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish()` is called\n89: - **THEN** options dict SHALL include: `version`, `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password`, `description`, `region`, `cloud_provider`, `node_port`, `replicas`, `namespace`\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Handle PublishRuntime exceptions\n92: - **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish()` raises an exception\n93: - **WHEN** exception is caught\n94: - **THEN** `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` SHALL be invoked\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Display publish success\n97: - **GIVEN** publish completes successfully\n98: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish()` returns result dict\n99: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print success message with agent endpoint and status using Rich formatting\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ### REQ-022.3: AgentCube Provider Prerequisites\n104: \n105: **Requirement:** The system SHALL validate that metadata contains required URLs for AgentCube provider deployment.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Router URL requirement\n108: - **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube`\n109: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url`\n110: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentCube provider requires router_url in agent_metadata.yaml\")`\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Workload manager URL requirement\n113: - **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube`\n114: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `workload_manager_url`\n115: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentCube provider requires workload_manager_url in agent_metadata.yaml\")`\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Both URLs present\n118: - **GIVEN** metadata contains both `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n119: - **WHEN** AgentCube publish proceeds\n120: - **THEN** validation SHALL pass\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ### REQ-022.4: Image Preparation Flow\n125: \n126: **Requirement:** The system SHALL prepare the container image for publishing via Docker push (local mode) or use explicit image URL.\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Local image preparation with Docker push\n129: - **GIVEN** build mode is `local` and no `--image-url` provided\n130: - **WHEN** `_prepare_local_image()` runs\n131: - **THEN** system SHALL push image to registry using `DockerService.push_image()`\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Image URL without credentials\n134: - **GIVEN** `--image-url` is provided but no credentials\n135: - **WHEN** image preparation runs\n136: - **THEN** system SHALL assume image is already pushed and use provided URL\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Image URL with credentials\n139: - **GIVEN** `--image-url`, `--image-username`, and `--image-password` are provided\n140: - **WHEN** image preparation runs\n141: - **THEN** system SHALL login, tag, and push image to specified URL\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Cloud image preparation\n144: - **GIVEN** build mode is `cloud`\n145: - **WHEN** `_prepare_cloud_image()` runs\n146: - **THEN** system SHALL use cloud provider's image registry URL\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Image tag from version\n149: - **GIVEN** metadata version is `1.2.3`\n150: - **WHEN** image is prepared\n151: - **THEN** image tag SHALL be `{agent_name}:1.2.3`\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### REQ-022.5: AgentCube CR Deployment\n156: \n157: **Requirement:** The system SHALL deploy AgentRuntime CR using `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` when provider is `agentcube`.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR creation\n160: - **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube` and prerequisites are met\n161: - **WHEN** `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` runs\n162: - **THEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` SHALL be called with agent spec\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Readiness probe configuration\n165: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `readiness_probe_path` and `readiness_probe_port`\n166: - **WHEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n167: - **THEN** readiness probe SHALL be configured in CR spec\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Environment variable injection\n170: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `workload_manager_url` and `router_url`\n171: - **WHEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n172: - **THEN** env vars `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` SHALL be set in pod spec\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Session timeout configuration\n175: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n176: - **WHEN** CR spec is assembled\n177: - **THEN** `sessionTimeout` SHALL be set to `\"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Image pull secret reference\n180: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n181: - **WHEN** CR spec is assembled\n182: - **THEN** `imagePullSecrets` SHALL reference `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR update\n185: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR already exists\n186: - **WHEN** publish is run again\n187: - **THEN** existing CR SHALL be patched/updated rather than recreated\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ### REQ-022.6: Standard Kubernetes Deployment\n192: \n193: **Requirement:** The system SHALL deploy standard Kubernetes Deployment + NodePort Service using `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` when provider is `k8s`.\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Kubernetes deployment creation\n196: - **GIVEN** provider is `k8s`\n197: - **WHEN** `_publish_k8s()` runs\n198: - **THEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` SHALL be called with deployment spec\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: NodePort allocation\n201: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--node-port 30080`\n202: - **WHEN** Service is created\n203: - **THEN** Service SHALL use specified NodePort\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Auto NodePort allocation\n206: - **GIVEN** user does not specify `--node-port`\n207: - **WHEN** Service is created\n208: - **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL allocate ephemeral NodePort (30000-32767)\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Replica count\n211: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--replicas 3`\n212: - **WHEN** Deployment is created\n213: - **THEN** Deployment spec SHALL have `replicas: 3`\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: Default replica count\n216: - **GIVEN** user does not specify `--replicas`\n217: - **WHEN** Deployment is created\n218: - **THEN** Deployment SHALL have `replicas: 1`\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: Deployment readiness wait\n221: - **GIVEN** Deployment is created\n222: - **WHEN** publish proceeds\n223: - **THEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name, timeout=120)` SHALL be called\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Deployment readiness timeout\n226: - **GIVEN** Deployment does not become ready within 120 seconds\n227: - **WHEN** wait completes\n228: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `TimeoutError(\"Deployment not ready after 120s\")`\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Service URL reporting\n231: - **GIVEN** Service is created with NodePort 30080\n232: - **WHEN** publish completes\n233: - **THEN** result SHALL include `service_url: \"http://localhost:30080\"`\n234: \n235: ---\n236: \n237: ### REQ-022.7: Namespace Management\n238: \n239: **Requirement:** The system SHALL ensure target namespace exists before deployment.\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: Namespace creation\n242: - **GIVEN** target namespace does not exist\n243: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` runs\n244: - **THEN** namespace SHALL be created via Kubernetes API\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: Namespace already exists\n247: - **GIVEN** target namespace exists\n248: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` runs\n249: - **THEN** no-op SHALL occur\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Default namespace\n252: - **GIVEN** user does not specify `--namespace`\n253: - **WHEN** deployment proceeds\n254: - **THEN** namespace SHALL default to `\"default\"`\n255: \n256: ---\n257: \n258: ### REQ-022.8: Publish Metadata Update\n259: \n260: **Requirement:** The system SHALL update workspace metadata with deployment information after successful publish.\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: Agent ID assignment\n263: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is created successfully\n264: - **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata()` runs\n265: - **THEN** metadata `agent_id` SHALL be set to CR name\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Agent endpoint recording\n268: - **GIVEN** deployment completes with service URL\n269: - **WHEN** metadata is updated\n270: - **THEN** metadata `agent_endpoint` SHALL be set to service URL\n271: \n272: #### Scenario: Session ID generation\n273: - **GIVEN** publish completes\n274: - **WHEN** metadata is updated\n275: - **THEN** metadata `session_id` SHALL be generated or preserved\n276: \n277: #### Scenario: Deployment info recording\n278: - **GIVEN** k8s provider deployment completes\n279: - **WHEN** metadata is updated\n280: - **THEN** metadata `k8s_deployment` SHALL include deployment name, service name, namespace, node_port\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: Metadata persistence\n283: - **GIVEN** metadata updates are made\n284: - **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata()` completes\n285: - **THEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` SHALL be written with `yaml.dump(exclude_none=True)`\n286: \n287: ---\n288: \n289: ### REQ-022.9: Publish Status Reporting\n290: \n291: **Requirement:** The system SHALL report publish results with deployment status, agent endpoint, and next steps.\n292: \n293: #### Scenario: Publish success output\n294: - **GIVEN** publish completes successfully\n295: - **WHEN** result is returned\n296: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print:\n297:   ```\n298:   ✓ Publish completed successfully\n299:   Agent: {agent_name}\n300:   Provider: {provider}\n301:   Endpoint: {agent_endpoint}\n302:   Status: {status}\n303:   ```\n304: \n305: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider success\n306: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is deployed\n307: - **WHEN** publish completes\n308: - **THEN** output SHALL include CR name and namespace\n309: \n310: #### Scenario: K8s provider success\n311: - **GIVEN** Deployment + Service are deployed\n312: - **WHEN** publish completes\n313: - **THEN** output SHALL include service URL and node port\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: Next step guidance\n316: - **GIVEN** publish succeeds\n317: - **WHEN** output is printed\n318: - **THEN** CLI SHALL suggest next command: `agentcube invoke` with appropriate flags\n319: \n320: ---\n321: \n322: ### REQ-022.10: Error Handling\n323: \n324: **Requirement:** The system SHALL handle publish failures with appropriate error messages and exit codes.\n325: \n326: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider prerequisite failure\n327: - **GIVEN** metadata lacks router_url\n328: - **WHEN** publish validation runs\n329: - **THEN** system SHALL print error in red and exit with code 1\n330: \n331: #### Scenario: Image push failure\n332: - **GIVEN** Docker push fails (auth error, network error)\n333: - **WHEN** image preparation runs\n334: - **THEN** error SHALL be reported and exit code 1 returned\n335: \n336: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API failure\n337: - **GIVEN** Kubernetes API is unreachable\n338: - **WHEN** deployment is attempted\n339: - **THEN** error SHALL be reported and exit code 1 returned\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: Deployment readiness failure\n342: - **GIVEN** Deployment fails to become ready\n343: - **WHEN** wait timeout expires\n344: - **THEN** error SHALL include pod events and exit code 1\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: CRD not installed\n347: - **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube` but CRD not installed\n348: - **WHEN** CR creation is attempted\n349: - **THEN** error SHALL indicate CRD is missing and exit with code 1\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ## Data Types\n354: \n355: ```python\n356: # Publish command options\n357: class PublishOptions(TypedDict, total=False):\n358:     workspace: str\n359:     version: Optional[str]\n360:     image_url: Optional[str]\n361:     image_username: Optional[str]\n362:     image_password: Optional[str]\n363:     description: Optional[str]\n364:     region: Optional[str]\n365:     cloud_provider: Optional[str]\n366:     provider: str  # \"agentcube\" or \"k8s\"\n367:     node_port: Optional[int]\n368:     replicas: Optional[int]\n369:     namespace: Optional[str]\n370:     verbose: bool\n371: \n372: # Publish result structure\n373: class PublishResult(TypedDict):\n374:     agent_name: str\n375:     provider: str\n376:     agent_id: Optional[str]\n377:     agent_endpoint: str\n378:     status: str\n379:     deployment_info: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]\n380:     publish_time: str\n381: ```\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ## CLI Flags Summary\n386: \n387: | Flag | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n388: |------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n389: | `--workspace` | `-f` | str | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace |\n390: | `--version` | - | Optional[str] | None | Semantic version string |\n391: | `--image-url` | - | Optional[str] | None | Image repository URL |\n392: | `--image-username` | - | Optional[str] | None | Image repository username |\n393: | `--image-password` | - | Optional[str] | None | Image repository password |\n394: | `--description` | - | Optional[str] | None | Agent description |\n395: | `--region` | - | Optional[str] | None | Deployment region |\n396: | `--cloud-provider` | - | Optional[str] | None | Cloud provider name |\n397: | `--provider` | - | str | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: agentcube or k8s |\n398: | `--node-port` | - | Optional[int] | None | NodePort for k8s Service |\n399: | `--replicas` | - | Optional[int] | None | Replicas for k8s Deployment |\n400: | `--namespace` | - | Optional[str] | None | Kubernetes namespace |\n401: | `--verbose` | - | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n402: \n403: ---\n404: \n405: ## Environment Variables\n406: \n407: | Variable | Description | Default |\n408: |----------|-------------|---------|\n409: | `KUBECONFIG` | Kubernetes config file | `~/.kube/config` |\n410: | `ROUTER_URL` | AgentCube router URL | - |\n411: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | AgentCube workload manager URL | - |\n412: | `DOCKER_HOST` | Docker daemon socket | system default |\n413: \n414: ---\n415: \n416: ## Error Codes\n417: \n418: | Error | Exit Code | Message |\n419: |-------|-----------|---------|\n420: | Missing router_url | 1 | \"AgentCube provider requires router_url in agent_metadata.yaml\" |\n421: | Missing workload_manager_url | 1 | \"AgentCube provider requires workload_manager_url in agent_metadata.yaml\" |\n422: | Image push failure | 1 | \"Failed to push image: {detail}\" |\n423: | Kubernetes API failure | 1 | \"Kubernetes API error: {detail}\" |\n424: | Deployment timeout | 1 | \"Deployment not ready after {timeout}s\" |\n425: | CRD not installed | 1 | \"AgentRuntime CRD not installed. Run: kubectl apply -f ...\" |\n426: | Invalid node-port | 1 | \"NodePort must be between 30000-32767\" |\n427: | Namespace creation failure | 1 | \"Failed to create namespace: {detail}\" |\n428: \n429: ---\n430: \n431: ## Dependencies\n432: \n433: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n434: |---------|---------|---------|\n435: | `typer[all]` | >=0.9.0 | CLI framework |\n436: | `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Data validation |\n437: | `docker` | >=6.0.0 | Docker SDK |\n438: | `rich` | >=13.0.0 | Output formatting |\n439: | `kubernetes` | >=28.0.0 | Kubernetes client |\n440: | `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | Metadata handling |\n441: | `httpx` | >=0.24.0 | HTTP client |\n442: \n443: ---\n444: \n445: ## Acceptance Checklist\n446: \n447: - [ ] `agentcube/cli/main.py` — publish command registered with Typer\n448: - [ ] `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` — PublishRuntime class implemented\n449: - [ ] `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` — AgentCubeProvider for CR deployment\n450: - [ ] `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` — KubernetesProvider for standard deployment\n451: - [ ] `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` — DockerService for image push\n452: - [ ] Image preparation flow (local push, cloud, explicit URL)\n453: - [ ] AgentCube CR deployment with readiness probe\n454: - [ ] K8s Deployment + NodePort Service deployment\n455: - [ ] Namespace management\n456: - [ ] Metadata update with deployment info\n457: - [ ] Success/failure output with Rich formatting\n458: - [ ] Verbose mode streams deployment logs\n459: - [ ] Error handling with appropriate exit codes\n460: - [ ] Next step guidance after successful publish\n461: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for publish path\n462: \n463: ---\n464: \n465: ## Open Questions\n466: \n467: 1. Should publish command support `--dry-run` for validation without deployment?\n468: 2. Should `--wait` flag be added to control readiness wait behavior?\n469: 3. Should publish support `--rollback` on deployment failure?\n470: 4. Should multi-region deployment be supported via `--region` flag?\n\n(End of file - total 470 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-022: CLI publish 命令\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** L  \n**Type:** Implementation of publish command for agent deployment to Kubernetes (AgentRuntime CR or standard Deployment/Service)\n\n**Base Specs:** cli-toolkit/design.md, cli-toolkit/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-022.1: Publish Command CLI Interface\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement the `publish` Typer subcommand with options for workspace, version, image repository credentials, deployment region, cloud provider, provider type (agentcube/k8s), node port, replicas, namespace, and verbose logging.\n\n#### Scenario: Publish command registration","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775876184007,"end":1775876184021}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876184026,"sessionID":"ses_2858832aeffeeNpWyuVMBY32Rn","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7812b4001wGbhAww8H732Zk","messageID":"msg_d7a77fc85001OyuUkvXSqzEbXp","sessionID":"ses_2858832aeffeeNpWyuVMBY32Rn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d50a35d84aa646a0afc881ff","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal_ar_028.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal_ar_028.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal implements the `AgentRuntimeClient` for the AgentCube Python SDK (`sdk-python`). The goal is to:\n6: \n7: 1. **Provide high-level agent invocation** - Abstract session bootstrapping and payload delivery to Agent Runtime workloads\n8: 2. **Enable agent communication** - Invoke agent runtimes with arbitrary JSON payloads through the Router\n9: 3. **Support context management** - Context manager protocol for automatic session cleanup and resource deallocation\n10: 4. **Ensure session lifecycle** - Bootstrap or reuse session ID from Agent Runtime invocation endpoint\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: **Module:** `sdk-python`  \n15: **Language:** Python  \n16: **Size:** M\n17: \n18: This AR covers:\n19: \n20: - **In scope:**\n21:   - `AgentRuntimeClient` class with context manager support\n22:   - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` for data plane HTTP operations via Router\n23:   - Session bootstrapping via GET on invocation endpoint\n24:   - Payload invocation via POST with session header\n25:   - HTTP session management with connection pooling\n26:   - Timeout configuration and per-call overrides\n27: \n28: - **Out of scope:**\n29:   - Direct user-facing CLI commands (separate AR)\n30:   - Kubernetes CRD management (handled by CLI toolkit)\n31:   - Code Interpreter functionality (covered by AR-027)\n32: \n33: ## Current State Analysis\n34: \n35: ### Existing Implementation\n36: \n37: Per the design specification (`python-sdk/design.md`), the following components are defined:\n38: \n39: 1. **Package Layout:**\n40:    - `agentcube/__init__.py` - Public exports (`CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient`)\n41:    - `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` - `AgentRuntimeClient` implementation\n42:    - `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` implementation\n43:    - `agentcube/utils/http.py` - `create_session` for HTTP session management\n44:    - `agentcube/utils/log.py` - `get_logger` for logging configuration\n45: \n46: 2. **Configuration Pattern:**\n47:    - No single `Configuration` class\n48:    - Distributed configuration: `AgentRuntimeClient` resolves `router_url` from argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable\n49:    - Timeout defaults: `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n50: \n51: 3. **HTTP Contracts:**\n52:    - Bootstrap: `GET {router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n53:    - Invoke: `POST {base_url}` with JSON payload and `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n54: \n55: ### Issues Identified\n56: \n57: 1. **Session header naming** - Must use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` for consistency with Code Interpreter\n58: 2. **Bootstrap validation** - Must raise `ValueError` if `x-agentcube-session-id` header is missing from bootstrap response\n59: 3. **Invoke precondition** - Must raise `ValueError` if `invoke()` is called without initialized `session_id`\n60: \n61: ## Proposed Changes\n62: \n63: ### 1. AgentRuntimeClient Implementation\n64: \n65: Implement in `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`:\n66: \n67: ```python\n68: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n69: \n70: from .clients.agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n71: from .utils.log import get_logger\n72: \n73: \n74: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n75:     \"\"\"High-level client for invoking Agent Runtime workloads.\n76:     \n77:     This client manages the session lifecycle for Agent Runtime invocations,\n78:     supporting both explicit session ID provision and automatic bootstrapping\n79:     from the Router invocation endpoint.\n80:     \n81:     Example usage:\n82:         # Context manager pattern (recommended)\n83:         with AgentRuntimeClient(\n84:             agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n85:             namespace=\"default\",\n86:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n87:         ) as client:\n88:             response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n89:             print(response.json())\n90:         \n91:         # Explicit session ID\n92:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n93:             agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n94:             session_id=\"pre-existing-session\"\n95:         )\n96:         try:\n97:             response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n98:         finally:\n99:             client.close()\n100:     \"\"\"\n101:     \n102:     def __init__(\n103:         self,\n104:         agent_name: str,\n105:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n106:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n107:         verbose: bool = False,\n108:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n109:         timeout: int = 120,\n110:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n111:     ) -> None:\n112:         \"\"\"Initialize AgentRuntimeClient.\n113:         \n114:         Args:\n115:             agent_name: Name of the target agent runtime\n116:             namespace: Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\")\n117:             router_url: Router base URL. Resolves from arg or ROUTER_URL env var\n118:             verbose: Enable debug logging\n119:             session_id: Existing session ID. If None, bootstraps new session\n120:             timeout: Default request timeout in seconds (default: 120)\n121:             connect_timeout: Connection timeout in seconds (default: 5.0)\n122:         \n123:         Raises:\n124:             ValueError: If router_url not provided and ROUTER_URL env var not set\n125:         \"\"\"\n126:         self.agent_name = agent_name\n127:         self.namespace = namespace\n128:         self.timeout = timeout\n129:         self.connect_timeout = connect_timeout\n130:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=\"DEBUG\" if verbose else \"INFO\")\n131:         \n132:         # Resolve router_url from argument or environment\n133:         self.router_url = router_url or os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n134:         if not self.router_url:\n135:             raise ValueError(\n136:                 \"router_url must be provided or ROUTER_URL environment variable must be set\"\n137:             )\n138:         \n139:         self.session_id = session_id\n140:         \n141:         # Initialize data plane client\n142:         self.dp_client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n143:             router_url=self.router_url,\n144:             namespace=self.namespace,\n145:             agent_name=self.agent_name,\n146:             timeout=self.timeout,\n147:             connect_timeout=self.connect_timeout,\n148:         )\n149:         \n150:         # Bootstrap session if not provided\n151:         if not self.session_id:\n152:             self.session_id = self.dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()\n153:             self.logger.debug(f\"Bootstrapped session_id: {self.session_id}\")\n154:     \n155:     def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\":\n156:         \"\"\"Context manager entry.\"\"\"\n157:         return self\n158:     \n159:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n160:         \"\"\"Context manager exit - ensures cleanup.\"\"\"\n161:         self.close()\n162:     \n163:     def invoke(\n164:         self,\n165:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n166:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n167:     ) -> Any:\n168:         \"\"\"Invoke the agent runtime with a JSON payload.\n169:         \n170:         Args:\n171:             payload: JSON-serializable dict to send to the agent\n172:             timeout: Optional per-call timeout override. If None, uses instance default\n173:         \n174:         Returns:\n175:             Agent response (typically parsed JSON or response object)\n176:         \n177:         Raises:\n178:             ValueError: If session_id is not initialized\n179:         \n180:         Example:\n181:             response = client.invoke({\n182:                 \"action\": \"query\",\n183:                 \"parameters\": {\"key\": \"value\"}\n184:             })\n185:         \"\"\"\n186:         if not self.session_id:\n187:             raise ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")\n188:         \n189:         self.logger.debug(f\"Invoking agent {self.agent_name} with payload: {payload}\")\n190:         \n191:         response = self.dp_client.invoke(\n192:             session_id=self.session_id,\n193:             payload=payload,\n194:             timeout=timeout,\n195:         )\n196:         \n197:         # Return parsed JSON response\n198:         return response.json()\n199:     \n200:     def close(self) -> None:\n201:         \"\"\"Close the underlying HTTP session.\n202:         \n203:         This method should be called when the client is no longer needed,\n204:         or use the context manager protocol for automatic cleanup.\n205:         \"\"\"\n206:         self.dp_client.close()\n207:         self.logger.debug(\"AgentRuntimeClient closed\")\n208: ```\n209: \n210: ### 2. AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Implementation\n211: \n212: Implement in `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`:\n213: \n214: ```python\n215: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n216: from urllib.parse import urljoin\n217: \n218: import requests\n219: \n220: from ..utils.http import create_session\n221: from ..utils.log import get_logger\n222: \n223: \n224: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n225:     \"\"\"Low-level HTTP client for Agent Runtime data plane operations.\n226:     \n227:     This client handles direct HTTP communication with the Router's\n228:     Agent Runtime invocation endpoint.\n229:     \"\"\"\n230:     \n231:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n232:     \n233:     def __init__(\n234:         self,\n235:         router_url: str,\n236:         namespace: str,\n237:         agent_name: str,\n238:         timeout: int = 120,\n239:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n240:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n241:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n242:     ) -> None:\n243:         \"\"\"Initialize AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.\n244:         \n245:         Args:\n246:             router_url: Router base URL\n247:             namespace: Kubernetes namespace\n248:             agent_name: Target agent runtime name\n249:             timeout: Request timeout in seconds (default: 120)\n250:             connect_timeout: Connection timeout in seconds (default: 5.0)\n251:             pool_connections: Number of connection pool slots\n252:             pool_maxsize: Maximum connections per host\n253:         \"\"\"\n254:         self.timeout = timeout\n255:         self.connect_timeout = connect_timeout\n256:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__)\n257:         \n258:         # Compute base URL: {router}/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{agent}/invocations/\n259:         base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n260:         self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n261:         \n262:         # Create HTTP session with connection pooling\n263:         self.session = create_session(\n264:             pool_connections=pool_connections,\n265:             pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize,\n266:         )\n267:         \n268:         # Set default session header\n269:         self.session.headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"] = \"\"  # Set per-request\n270:     \n271:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n272:         \"\"\"Bootstrap a new session ID from the invocation endpoint.\n273:         \n274:         Makes a GET request to the base invocation URL to obtain\n275:         a session ID from the response header.\n276:         \n277:         Returns:\n278:             Session ID from x-agentcube-session-id header\n279:         \n280:         Raises:\n281:             ValueError: If x-agentcube-session-id header is missing\n282:         \"\"\"\n283:         self.logger.debug(f\"Bootstrapping session from {self.base_url}\")\n284:         \n285:         response = self.session.get(\n286:             self.base_url,\n287:             timeout=(self.connect_timeout, self.timeout),\n288:         )\n289:         response.raise_for_status()\n290:         \n291:         session_id = response.headers.get(\"x-agentcube-session-id\")\n292:         if not session_id:\n293:             raise ValueError(\n294:                 \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"\n295:             )\n296:         \n297:         # Set session header for subsequent requests\n298:         self.session.headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"] = session_id\n299:         \n300:         return session_id\n301:     \n302:     def invoke(\n303:         self,\n304:         session_id: str,\n305:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n306:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n307:     ) -> requests.Response:\n308:         \"\"\"Invoke the agent runtime with a JSON payload.\n309:         \n310:         Args:\n311:             session_id: Session identifier for request header\n312:             payload: JSON-serializable dict to send\n313:             timeout: Optional timeout override. If tuple, uses (connect, read)\n314:         \n315:         Returns:\n316:             requests.Response object from the POST request\n317:         \n318:         Raises:\n319:             requests.RequestException: On HTTP errors\n320:         \"\"\"\n321:         # Set session header for this request\n322:         headers = {self.SESSION_HEADER: session_id, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}\n323:         \n324:         # Compute effective timeout\n325:         if timeout is None:\n326:             effective_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, self.timeout)\n327:         elif isinstance(timeout, tuple):\n328:             effective_timeout = timeout\n329:         else:\n330:             effective_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, timeout)\n331:         \n332:         self.logger.debug(f\"POST {self.base_url} with payload: {payload}\")\n333:         \n334:         response = self.session.post(\n335:             self.base_url,\n336:             json=payload,\n337:             headers=headers,\n338:             timeout=effective_timeout,\n339:         )\n340:         \n341:         response.raise_for_status()\n342:         return response\n343:     \n344:     def close(self) -> None:\n345:         \"\"\"Close the underlying HTTP session.\"\"\"\n346:         self.session.close()\n347:         self.logger.debug(\"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient closed\")\n348: ```\n349: \n350: ### 3. Module Exports\n351: \n352: Update `agentcube/__init__.py`:\n353: \n354: ```python\n355: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n356: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n357: \n358: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n359: ```\n360: \n361: Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`:\n362: \n363: ```python\n364: from .control_plane import ControlPlaneClient\n365: from .code_interpreter_data_plane import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n366: from .agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n367: \n368: __all__ = [\n369:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n370:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n371:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n372: ]\n373: ```\n374: \n375: ## Impact Analysis\n376: \n377: ### Files to Create\n378: \n379: | File | Purpose |\n380: |------|---------|\n381: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` implementation |\n382: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` implementation |\n383: \n384: ### Files to Modify\n385: \n386: | File | Changes | Impact |\n387: |------|---------|--------|\n388: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Export `AgentRuntimeClient` | Low - additive |\n389: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-export `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Low - convenience |\n390: \n391: ### Dependencies\n392: \n393: From `pyproject.toml`:\n394: \n395: ```toml\n396: dependencies = [\n397:     \"requests\",              # HTTP client\n398:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",         # JWT token handling (if needed)\n399:     \"cryptography\",          # Cryptographic operations (if needed)\n400: ]\n401: \n402: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n403: ```\n404: \n405: ### Backward Compatibility\n406: \n407: - **No breaking changes** - This is a new feature addition\n408: - **Session header consistency** - Uses lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` matching Code Interpreter\n409: - **Timeout defaults** - Consistent 120s read / 5.0s connect defaults across all clients\n410: \n411: ### Testing Impact\n412: \n413: Unit tests required for:\n414: \n415: - `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__()` with/without session_id\n416: - `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()` payload delivery\n417: - `AgentRuntimeClient` context manager cleanup\n418: - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()` header extraction\n419: - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke()` timeout handling\n420: - Error cases: missing router_url, missing session header, invoke without session\n421: \n422: ## Alternatives Considered\n423: \n424: ### Alternative 1: Reuse CodeInterpreterClient Pattern\n425: \n426: Extend `CodeInterpreterClient` to support agent invocation.\n427: \n428: **Pros:**\n429: - Single client class for both use cases\n430: - Shared session management logic\n431: \n432: **Cons:**\n433: - Violates single responsibility principle\n434: - Confuses distinct use cases (code execution vs agent invocation)\n435: - Different HTTP contracts (Code Interpreter has files API, Agent Runtime does not)\n436: \n437: **Decision:** Separate client classes maintain clear separation of concerns.\n438: \n439: ### Alternative 2: Async/Await HTTP Client\n440: \n441: Use `aiohttp` instead of `requests` for async operations.\n442: \n443: **Pros:**\n444: - Better performance for concurrent invocations\n445: - Modern async pattern\n446: \n447: **Cons:**\n448: - Breaking change from synchronous Code Interpreter pattern\n449: - Requires async context manager support throughout\n450: - Increased complexity for users unfamiliar with async\n451: \n452: **Decision:** Synchronous `requests` maintains consistency with existing SDK.\n453: \n454: ### Alternative 3: Session ID from Control Plane\n455: \n456: Bootstrap session ID via control plane instead of data plane GET.\n457: \n458: **Pros:**\n459: - Centralized session management\n460: - Consistent with Code Interpreter session creation\n461: \n462: **Cons:**\n463: - Requires control plane API changes\n464: - Agent Runtime sessions are Router-scoped, not Workload Manager-scoped\n465: - Adds unnecessary round-trip\n466: \n467: **Decision:** Bootstrap via data plane GET is more direct and aligns with Router architecture.\n468: \n469: ### Alternative 4: Explicit Session Management\n470: \n471: Require users to always provide session_id explicitly.\n472: \n473: **Pros:**\n474: - Simpler implementation (no bootstrap logic)\n475: - Users have full control over session lifecycle\n476: \n477: **Cons:**\n478: - Poor user experience (must manage sessions externally)\n479: - Loses convenience of context manager pattern\n480: - Inconsistent with CodeInterpreterClient pattern\n481: \n482: **Decision:** Automatic bootstrapping provides better developer experience.\n483: \n484: ## Implementation Checklist\n485: \n486: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` in `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n487: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n488: - [ ] Export `AgentRuntimeClient` in `agentcube/__init__.py`\n489: - [ ] Export `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n490: - [ ] Write unit tests for session bootstrapping\n491: - [ ] Write unit tests for invoke with/without timeout\n492: - [ ] Write unit tests for context manager cleanup\n493: - [ ] Write integration tests with live Router endpoint\n494: - [ ] Add usage examples to `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py`\n495: - [ ] Update README with AgentRuntimeClient documentation\n496: \n497: ## Testing Strategy\n498: \n499: ### Unit Tests\n500: \n501: ```python\n502: # tests/unit/test_agent_runtime.py\n503: \n504: import pytest\n505: from unittest.mock import Mock, patch\n506: from agentcube.agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n507: from agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n508: \n509: \n510: class TestAgentRuntimeClient:\n511:     \n512:     @patch('agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient')\n513:     def test_init_with_session_id(self, mock_dp_client):\n514:         \"\"\"Test initialization with explicit session_id.\"\"\"\n515:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n516:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n517:             namespace=\"default\",\n518:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n519:             session_id=\"pre-existing-session\"\n520:         )\n521:         \n522:         assert client.session_id == \"pre-existing-session\"\n523:         mock_dp_client.assert_called_once()\n524:     \n525:     @patch('agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient')\n526:     def test_init_without_session_id_bootstrap(self, mock_dp_client):\n527:         \"\"\"Test initialization triggers bootstrap.\"\"\"\n528:         mock_dp_client.return_value.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"bootstrapped-123\"\n529:         \n530:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n531:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n532:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n533:         )\n534:         \n535:         assert client.session_id == \"bootstrapped-123\"\n536:         mock_dp_client.return_value.bootstrap_session_id.assert_called_once()\n537:     \n538:     @patch.dict('os.environ', {}, clear=True)\n539:     def test_init_missing_router_url_raises(self):\n540:         \"\"\"Test missing router_url raises ValueError.\"\"\"\n541:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"router_url must be provided\"):\n542:             AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\")\n543:     \n544:     @patch('agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient')\n545:     def test_invoke_success(self, mock_dp_client):\n546:         \"\"\"Test successful invoke.\"\"\"\n547:         mock_response = Mock()\n548:         mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\"}\n549:         mock_dp_client.return_value.invoke.return_value = mock_response\n550:         \n551:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n552:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n553:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n554:             session_id=\"test-session\"\n555:         )\n556:         \n557:         result = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n558:         \n559:         assert result == {\"result\": \"success\"}\n560:         mock_dp_client.return_value.invoke.assert_called_once()\n561:     \n562:     @patch('agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient')\n563:     def test_invoke_without_session_raises(self, mock_dp_client):\n564:         \"\"\"Test invoke without session_id raises ValueError.\"\"\"\n565:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n566:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n567:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n568:         )\n569:         client.session_id = None  # Simulate uninitialized state\n570:         \n571:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"session_id is not initialized\"):\n572:             client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n573:     \n574:     @patch('agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient')\n575:     def test_context_manager(self, mock_dp_client):\n576:         \"\"\"Test context manager cleanup.\"\"\"\n577:         with AgentRuntimeClient(\n578:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n579:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n580:         ) as client:\n581:             assert client is not None\n582:         \n583:         mock_dp_client.return_value.close.assert_called_once()\n584: \n585: \n586: class TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n587:     \n588:     @patch('agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane.create_session')\n589:     def test_bootstrap_session_id_success(self, mock_create_session):\n590:         \"\"\"Test successful session bootstrap.\"\"\"\n591:         mock_session = Mock()\n592:         mock_session.get.return_value.headers = {\n593:             \"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"bootstrapped-456\"\n594:         }\n595:         mock_create_session.return_value = mock_session\n596:         \n597:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n598:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n599:             namespace=\"default\",\n600:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n601:         )\n602:         \n603:         session_id = client.bootstrap_session_id()\n604:         \n605:         assert session_id == \"bootstrapped-456\"\n606:         mock_session.get.assert_called_once()\n607:     \n608:     @patch('agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane.create_session')\n609:     def test_bootstrap_session_id_missing_header_raises(self, mock_create_session):\n610:         \"\"\"Test missing session header raises ValueError.\"\"\"\n611:         mock_session = Mock()\n612:         mock_session.get.return_value.headers = {}\n613:         mock_create_session.return_value = mock_session\n614:         \n615:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n616:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n617:             namespace=\"default\",\n618:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n619:         )\n620:         \n621:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Missing required response header\"):\n622:             client.bootstrap_session_id()\n623:     \n624:     @patch('agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane.create_session')\n625:     def test_invoke_with_timeout_override(self, mock_create_session):\n626:         \"\"\"Test invoke with per-call timeout override.\"\"\"\n627:         mock_session = Mock()\n628:         mock_create_session.return_value = mock_session\n629:         \n630:         client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n631:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n632:             namespace=\"default\",\n633:             agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n634:         )\n635:         \n636:         client.invoke(session_id=\"test-123\", payload={\"msg\": \"hi\"}, timeout=60)\n637:         \n638:         # Verify timeout was overridden\n639:         call_args = mock_session.post.call_args\n640:         assert call_args[1][\"timeout\"] == (5.0, 60)  # (connect, read)\n641: ```\n642: \n643: ### Integration Tests\n644: \n645: ```python\n646: # tests/integration/test_agent_runtime_integration.py\n647: \n648: import os\n649: import pytest\n650: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n651: \n652: \n653: @pytest.fixture\n654: def agent_runtime_client():\n655:     \"\"\"Integration test fixture.\"\"\"\n656:     client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n657:         agent_name=os.getenv(\"TEST_AGENT_NAME\", \"test-agent\"),\n658:         router_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"),\n659:         namespace=\"test\"\n660:     )\n661:     yield client\n662:     client.close()\n663: \n664: \n665: @pytest.mark.integration\n666: def test_agent_invoke_full_flow(agent_runtime_client):\n667:     \"\"\"Test full agent invocation flow.\"\"\"\n668:     response = agent_runtime_client.invoke({\n669:         \"action\": \"echo\",\n670:         \"message\": \"integration test\"\n671:     })\n672:     \n673:     assert response is not None\n674:     assert \"message\" in response or \"result\" in response\n675: \n676: \n677: @pytest.mark.integration\n678: def test_context_manager_cleanup():\n679:     \"\"\"Test context manager ensures cleanup.\"\"\"\n680:     with AgentRuntimeClient(\n681:         agent_name=os.getenv(\"TEST_AGENT_NAME\", \"test-agent\"),\n682:         router_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"),\n683:         namespace=\"test\"\n684:     ) as client:\n685:         response = client.invoke({\"action\": \"test\"})\n686:         assert response is not None\n687:     \n688:     # Client closed automatically\n689: ```\n690: \n691: ### End-to-End Test\n692: \n693: ```python\n694: # scripts/e2e_agent_runtime_test.py\n695: \n696: #!/usr/bin/env python3\n697: \"\"\"End-to-end test for Agent Runtime Client\"\"\"\n698: \n699: import sys\n700: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n701: \n702: \n703: def main():\n704:     with AgentRuntimeClient(\n705:         agent_name=\"echo-agent\",\n706:         router_url=\"http://localhost:8080\",\n707:         namespace=\"default\"\n708:     ) as client:\n709:         # Test 1: Simple invoke\n710:         response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n711:         assert \"message\" in response or \"result\" in response\n712:         \n713:         # Test 2: Complex payload\n714:         response = client.invoke({\n715:             \"action\": \"compute\",\n716:             \"data\": {\"a\": 1, \"b\": 2}\n717:         })\n718:         assert response is not None\n719:         \n720:     print(\"All Agent Runtime E2E tests passed!\")\n721:     return 0\n722: \n723: \n724: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n725:     sys.exit(main())\n726: ```\n727: \n728: ## Future Considerations\n729: \n730: 1. **Streaming responses** - Support for streaming agent responses via SSE or chunked transfer\n731: 2. **Retry logic** - Automatic retry with exponential backoff for transient failures\n732: 3. **Async support** - Async/await variant for concurrent agent invocations\n733: 4. **Agent discovery** - List available agent runtimes in namespace\n734: 5. **Session metadata** - Expose session metadata (creation time, TTL) from bootstrap response\n735: 6. **Batch invocations** - Support for batch processing multiple payloads\n736: \n737: ## References\n738: \n739: - SDK Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n740: - SDK Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n741: - Code Interpreter Client: AR-027\n742: - Router API: `session-router/design.md`\n743: \n744: ## Acceptance Criteria\n745: \n746: | Criterion | Verification |\n747: |-----------|--------------|\n748: | `AgentRuntimeClient` bootstraps session | GET invocation URL returns `x-agentcube-session-id` |\n749: | `AgentRuntimeClient` reuses session_id | Explicit session_id skips bootstrap |\n750: | `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()` sends payload | POST with JSON body and session header |\n751: | Context manager cleanup | `close()` called on exit |\n752: | Missing router_url raises | `ValueError` when neither arg nor env var set |\n753: | Missing session header raises | `ValueError` if bootstrap response lacks header |\n754: | Invoke without session raises | `ValueError` if `invoke()` called without session_id |\n755: | Timeout override works | Per-call `timeout` parameter honored |\n756: | Exports in `__all__` | `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient` works |\n757: \n758: ---\n759: \n760: **Document Version:** 1.0  \n761: **Last Updated:** 2026-04-11  \n762: **Author:** AgentCube Team  \n763: **Contact:** agentcube@volcano.sh  \n764: **AR:** AR-028  \n765: **Module:** `sdk-python`\n\n(End of file - total 765 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the `AgentRuntimeClient` for the AgentCube Python SDK (`sdk-python`). The goal is to:\n\n1. **Provide high-level agent invocation** - Abstract session bootstrapping and payload delivery to Agent Runtime workloads\n2. **Enable agent communication** - Invoke agent runtimes with arbitrary JSON payloads through the Router\n3. **Support context management** - Context manager protocol for automatic session cleanup and resource deallocation\n4. **Ensure session lifecycle** - Bootstrap or reuse session ID from Agent Runtime invocation endpoint\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal_ar_028.md","time":{"start":1775876184010,"end":1775876184024}}}}
