{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876261695,"sessionID":"ses_2858832aeffeeNpWyuVMBY32Rn","part":{"id":"prt_d7a782e13001kqqdg5cs4GjaLQ","messageID":"msg_d7a781814001gpFVhh3HhRnkus","sessionID":"ses_2858832aeffeeNpWyuVMBY32Rn","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_ed3acd699bb7416bb683735b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification — AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Implementation of AgentRuntimeClient for invoking Agent Runtime workloads via Router\n\n**Base Specs:** python-sdk/design.md, python-sdk/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-028.1: AgentRuntimeClient Initialization\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeClient` class with configuration resolution for router_url, session_id, and timeout parameters.\n\n#### Scenario: Initialize with explicit session_id\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is provided to `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.session_id` SHALL be set to the provided value and bootstrap SHALL NOT be called\n\n#### Scenario: Initialize without session_id triggers bootstrap\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` SHALL be called and result assigned to `self.session_id`\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL from argument\n- **GIVEN** `router_url` is provided as argument\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL be set to the provided argument\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL from environment variable\n- **GIVEN** `router_url` is `None` and `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL be set from `os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Missing router_url raises ValueError\n- **GIVEN** `router_url` is `None` and `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is not set\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message containing \"router_url must be provided\"\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout defaults\n- **GIVEN** `timeout` and `connect_timeout` are not specified\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL default to `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL default to `5.0`\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace default\n- **GIVEN** `namespace` is not specified\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose logging configuration\n- **GIVEN** `verbose=True` is specified\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** logger level SHALL be set to `DEBUG`\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose default is False\n- **GIVEN** `verbose` is not specified\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** logger level SHALL default to `INFO`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-028.2: AgentRuntimeClient Context Manager\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement context manager protocol (`__enter__`, `__exit__`) for automatic resource cleanup.\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager entry\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used in `with` statement\n- **WHEN** entering the context\n- **THEN** `__enter__` SHALL return `self`\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager normal exit\n- **GIVEN** context block completes without exception\n- **WHEN** exiting the context\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()`\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager exception exit\n- **GIVEN** context block raises an exception\n- **WHEN** exiting the context\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()` and allow exception to propagate\n\n---\n\n### REQ-028.3: AgentRuntimeClient.invoke Method\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `invoke(payload, timeout=None)` method for sending JSON payloads to the agent runtime.\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with payload\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is initialized\n- **WHEN** `invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `dp_client.invoke()` with session_id and payload\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke returns parsed JSON\n- **GIVEN** `dp_client.invoke()` returns a response object\n- **WHEN** `invoke()` completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `response.json()` (parsed JSON)\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke without session_id raises\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or falsy\n- **WHEN** `invoke()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke with timeout override\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=60)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** timeout `60` SHALL be passed to `dp_client.invoke()`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke without timeout uses default\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(payload)` is called without timeout\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** `timeout=None` SHALL be passed to `dp_client.invoke()` (uses instance default)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-028.4: AgentRuntimeClient.close Method\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `close()` method for closing the underlying HTTP session.\n\n#### Scenario: Close calls dp_client.close\n- **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `self.dp_client.close()`\n\n#### Scenario: Close logs debug message\n- **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n- **WHEN** the method completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL log debug message \"AgentRuntimeClient closed\"\n\n---\n\n### REQ-028.5: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Initialization\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with base URL computation from router_url, namespace, and agent_name.\n\n#### Scenario: Base URL computation\n- **GIVEN** `router_url=\"http://router:8080\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `agent_name=\"test-agent\"`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/test-agent/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: Session constant\n- **GIVEN** class is defined\n- **WHEN** accessed\n- **THEN** `SESSION_HEADER` SHALL equal `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n#### Scenario: HTTP session creation with pooling\n- **GIVEN** client initializes\n- **WHEN** `create_session()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10` by default\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout defaults\n- **GIVEN** `timeout` and `connect_timeout` are not specified\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL default to `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL default to `5.0`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-028.6: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `bootstrap_session_id()` method that GETs the invocation URL and extracts session ID from response header.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful session bootstrap\n- **GIVEN** Router responds with `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return the header value\n\n#### Scenario: Missing session header raises\n- **GIVEN** Router response lacks `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap sets session header\n- **GIVEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` succeeds\n- **WHEN** it completes\n- **THEN** `self.session.headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"]` SHALL be set to the bootstrapped value\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap makes GET request\n- **GIVEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `GET self.base_url` with timeout `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-028.7: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout=None)` method for POSTing JSON payloads to the agent runtime.\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke sends POST request\n- **GIVEN** `invoke()` is called with payload\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `POST self.base_url` with JSON body\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke sets session header\n- **GIVEN** `invoke()` is called\n- **WHEN** headers are set\n- **THEN** `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` SHALL be included\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke sets Content-Type header\n- **GIVEN** `invoke()` is called\n- **WHEN** headers are set\n- **THEN** `Content-Type: application/json` SHALL be included\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple default\n- **GIVEN** `invoke()` is called without timeout\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` tuple\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke timeout override\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=60)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, 60)`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke returns response object\n- **GIVEN** `invoke()` completes successfully\n- **WHEN** response is received\n- **THEN** it SHALL return the `requests.Response` object\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke raises on HTTP error\n- **GIVEN** Server returns HTTP error status\n- **WHEN** `invoke()` receives response\n- **THEN** `response.raise_for_status()` SHALL be called (raises `requests.HTTPError`)\n\n---\n\n### REQ-028.8: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.close\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement `close()` method for closing the underlying HTTP session.\n\n#### Scenario: Close calls session.close\n- **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `self.session.close()`\n\n#### Scenario: Close logs debug message\n- **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n- **WHEN** the method completes\n- **THEN** logger SHALL log debug message \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient closed\"\n\n---\n\n### REQ-028.9: Module Exports\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL export `AgentRuntimeClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in appropriate `__init__.py` files.\n\n#### Scenario: Root package exports AgentRuntimeClient\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/__init__.py` is imported\n- **WHEN** `__all__` is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `\"AgentRuntimeClient\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Import AgentRuntimeClient from root\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube` package is installed\n- **WHEN** `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient` is executed\n- **THEN** import SHALL succeed\n\n#### Scenario: Clients subpackage exports AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` is imported\n- **WHEN** `__all__` is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `\"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient from clients\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube` package is installed\n- **WHEN** `from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is executed\n- **THEN** import SHALL succeed\n\n---\n\n### REQ-028.10: Session Header Naming\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for all SDK Router requests.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient SESSION_HEADER constant\n- **GIVEN** class constant `SESSION_HEADER` is defined\n- **WHEN** accessed\n- **THEN** it SHALL equal `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"` (lowercase)\n\n#### Scenario: Bootstrap header extraction\n- **GIVEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` reads response header\n- **WHEN** extracting header value\n- **THEN** it SHALL use lowercase key `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke request header\n- **GIVEN** `invoke()` sets request headers\n- **WHEN** header dict is constructed\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"` as key (lowercase)\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n```python\n# AgentRuntimeClient constructor signature\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    ) -> None: ...\n\n# AgentRuntimeClient public methods\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\": ...\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n    def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n\n# AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructor signature\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        agent_name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ) -> None: ...\n\n# AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient public methods\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n    ) -> requests.Response: ...\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## HTTP Contracts\n\n### Agent Runtime Data Plane\n\n| Operation | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n|-----------|--------|-----|---------|------|\n| Bootstrap session | GET | `{router}/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{agent}/invocations/` | (none) | (none) |\n| Invoke agent | POST | `{base_url}` | `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `{\"key\": \"value\", ...}` |\n\n### Response Headers\n\n| Header | Purpose | Required |\n|--------|---------|----------|\n| `x-agentcube-session-id` | Session identifier from bootstrap | Yes (on GET) |\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n| Error | Condition | Exception Type |\n|-------|-----------|----------------|\n| Missing router_url | Neither argument nor `ROUTER_URL` env var provided | `ValueError` |\n| Missing session header | Bootstrap response lacks `x-agentcube-session-id` | `ValueError` |\n| Invoke without session | `invoke()` called with falsy `session_id` | `ValueError` |\n| HTTP error | Server returns 4xx/5xx status | `requests.HTTPError` |\n| Network error | Connection refused, timeout, etc. | `requests.RequestException` |\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description | Default |\n|----------|-------------|---------|\n| `ROUTER_URL` | Router base URL for Agent Runtime | (required) |\n| `LOG_LEVEL` | Logging level (if used by get_logger) | INFO |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\nFrom `pyproject.toml`:\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",              # HTTP client\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",         # JWT token handling\n    \"cryptography\",          # Cryptographic operations\n]\n\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Checklist\n\n- [ ] `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` — `AgentRuntimeClient` class implemented\n- [ ] `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` — `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class implemented\n- [ ] `agentcube/__init__.py` — exports `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`\n- [ ] `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` — exports `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in `__all__`\n- [ ] Router URL resolution from argument or `ROUTER_URL` env var\n- [ ] Session bootstrapping via GET on invocation endpoint\n- [ ] Payload invocation via POST with session header\n- [ ] Context manager protocol (`__enter__`, `__exit__`)\n- [ ] `invoke()` raises `ValueError` without initialized session\n- [ ] Bootstrap raises `ValueError` if header missing\n- [ ] Timeout defaults: 120s read / 5.0s connect\n- [ ] Per-call timeout override support\n- [ ] HTTP session with connection pooling (10/10)\n- [ ] Lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` header usage\n- [ ] Unit tests for session bootstrapping\n- [ ] Unit tests for invoke with/without timeout\n- [ ] Unit tests for context manager cleanup\n- [ ] Unit tests for error cases\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for AgentRuntimeClient\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Should `invoke()` expose additional response metadata beyond parsed JSON (e.g., status code, headers)?\n2. Should retry logic be added for transient HTTP failures?\n3. Should streaming response support be added for long-running agent operations?\n4. Should agent runtime discovery (list available agents) be supported?\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775876261680,"end":1775876261692}}}}
